# Routing Rules

- Source of truth for route registration is `src/routes/AppRoutes.tsx`.
- Every route must map to exactly one page component.
- If a route is added/removed/renamed, update:
  - `src/routes/AppRoutes.tsx`
  - `docs/routes-overview.md`
  - `docs/role-matrix.md` when access changes
- Keep legacy redirects when they preserve bookmarked flows.
- Unknown routes must fall back to the 404 route.

# Protected Access

- Use `ProtectedRoute` for role-gated screens.
- Never rely on UI-only hiding for access control.
- For shared routes, list all allowed roles explicitly in route config.

# Wizard Rules

- Booking/setup deep links must validate prior state.
- Invalid step state must redirect to the first valid step.
- Preserve query-driven step behavior for wizard flows.
